## 7. How to Inspect This in Your Project

* **Files to Check:** Check `src/components/Ticker/StockTicker.tsx`, `CryptoHeatmap.tsx`, `ForexHeatmap.tsx`, etc.
* **Identify External Widgets:** Look for `document.createElement('script')` and `script.src = 'https://s3.tradingview.com/...'`.
* **Inspect Browser Network Tab:** 
  1. Open Chrome DevTools (F12) -> Network tab.
  2. Filter by `tradingview`. You will see the `.js` file being downloaded.
  3. Change the filter to `WS` (WebSockets) to see the live data stream TradingView opens under the hood.
* **Inspect the DOM:** Right-click the ticker in the browser and select "Inspect". You will see an `<iframe>` tag that is not present in your React source code—it was injected dynamically.

